0Beyond%20her%20record%20of%20supporting%20legalization%2C%20she's%20served%20in%20an%20administration%20that's%20issued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-pardons-marijuana-offenders-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethousands%20of%20pardons%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20marijuana%20use%20and%20possession.%20After%20the%20Biden%20administration%20initiated%20a%20process%20this%20year%20to%20reclassify%20marijuana%20from%20a%20Schedule%20I%20to%20a%20Schedule%20III%20drug%2C%20signifying%20that%20the%20government%20views%20it%20as%20less%20dangerous%2C%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fspeeches-remarks%2F2024%2F03%2F15%2Fremarks-by-vice-president-harris-in-a-roundtable-conversation-about-marijuana-reform%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Babsurd%26quot%3B%20that%20marijuana%20was%20treated%20as%20a%20dangerous%20drug%20akin%20to%20heroin%20or%20fentanyl.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20Harris%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FKamalaHarris%2Fstatus%2F1781779896580088222%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20nobody%20%26quot%3Bshould%20have%20to%20go%20to%20jail%20for%20smoking%20weed%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20must%20continue%20to%20change%20our%20nation's%20approach%20to%20marijuana.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Harris'%20willingness%20to%20go%20beyond%20what%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20done%20carries%20not%20just%20significant%20economic%20implications%20%E2%80%94%20states%20collected%20more%20than%20%244%20billion%20in%20tax%20revenue%20in%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mpp.org%2Fissues%2Flegalization%2Fcannabis-tax-revenue-states-regulate-cannabis-adult-use%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Marijuana%20Policy%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20political%20ramifications%20in%20this%20election%2C%20given%20that%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20recently%20signaled%20support%20for%20legalization%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterviews%20with%20more%20than%20a%20half-dozen%20pro-marijuana%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%20this%20week%20revealed%20that%20many%20are%20not%20entirely%20sure%20of%20Harris'%20current%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20don't%20know%20where%20she%20is%20on%20this%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Jim%20Himes%20of%20Connecticut%2C%20a%20key%20sponsor%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcannabis-banking-bill-safe-act-congress-marijuana-credit-debit-card-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bsafe%20banking%26quot%3B%20legislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20designed%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20banks%20to%20work%20with%20marjiuana%20businesses%20in%20states%20where%20the%20drug%20is%20legal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20suspect%20that%20she%20would%20probably%20support%20%5Blegalization%5D%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Democratic%20Sen.%20John%20Fetterman%20of%20Pennsylvania.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Earl%20Blumenauer%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20seemed%20flabbergasted%20by%20the%20question.%20The%20Oregon%20Democrat%2C%20who%20was%20a%20founder%20of%20the%20Congressional%20Cannabis%20Caucus%2C%20insisted%20that%20Harris'%20past%20cosponsorship%20of%20pro-marijuana%20bills%20was%20sufficient%20for%20understanding%20her%20current%20stance.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20going%20to%20change.%20Jeez%2C%26quot%3B%20Blumenauer%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20her%20record.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBooker%2C%20a%20longtime%20champion%20for%20marijuana%20reform%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%2C%20pointed%20to%20Harris'%20introduction%20of%20the%20Marijuana%20Opportunity%20Reinvestment%20and%20Expungement%20Act%20in%202019%2C%20even%20as%20he%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration%20had%20not%20gone%20as%20far%20as%20that%20bill%20would.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20that%20there%20are%20principles%20in%20there%20that%20are%20still%20her%20principles%2C%26quot%3B%20Booker%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Harris%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bguided%20by%20the%20pragmatism%2C%20and%20this%20institution%2C%20and%20what%20can%20we%20can%20get%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Alexandria%20Ocasio-Cortez%20speculated%20that%20Harris%20had%20played%20a%20role%20in%20pushing%20the%20Biden%20administration%20to%20take%20a%20more%20progressive%20approach%20to%20marijuana%2C%20including%20the%20move%20to%20reschedule%20the%20drug%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20believe%20that%20the%20President%20was%20naturally%20positioned%20to%20do%20that.%20I%20think%20he%20is%2C%20in%20several%20respects%2C%20of%20his%20generation%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20New%20York%20Democrat.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20that%20push%20did%20come%20from%20the%20Vice%20President.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229595cd58-0e20-44c7-a8a8-ef9457bd4faa%5C%22%3E'I%20don't%20know%20whether%20that%20would%20be%20a%20top%20priority%20issue'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20denying%20that%20marijuana%20legalization%20is%20popular.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F514007%2Fgrassroots-support-legalizing-marijuana-hits-record.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20Gallup%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2070%25%20of%20Americans%20believed%20the%20drug%20should%20be%20legal%2C%20including%20a%20bare%20majority%20of%20Republicans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20why%20Trump%20has%20broken%20with%20GOP%20orthodoxy%20and%20announced%20that%20he%20would%20vote%20for%20a%20ballot%20measure%20to%20legalize%20recreational%20marijuana%20use%20in%20Florida%20and%20said%20he%20would%20support%20safe%20banking%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there's%20reason%20for%20skepticism%20around%20Trump's%20position%20%E2%80%94%20as%20president%2C%20he%20was%20not%20especially%20friendly%20toward%20marijuana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20impossible%20to%20tell%20from%20supportive%20statements%20whether%20or%20not%20he%20would%20actually%20take%20any%20action%20on%20this%20issue%20as%20president%2C%20considering%20he%20really%20didn't%20touch%20it%20at%20all%20in%20his%20last%20administration%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Morgan%20Fox%2C%20political%20director%20for%20the%20National%20Organization%20for%20the%20Reform%20of%20Marijuana%20Laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFox%20said%20that%20while%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20%26quot%3Bdone%20more%20for%20cannabis%20policy%20reform%20than%20any%20presidency%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20move%20to%20reschedule%20marijuana%20did%20not%20go%20far%20enough%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20may%20be%20months%20until%20it%20actually%20takes%20effect%20as%20the%20review%20process%20plays%20out.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20%26quot%3Bpractical%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20Fox%20said%2C%20is%20that%20marijuana%20businesses%20would%20now%20be%20allowed%20to%20deduct%20business%20expenses%20on%20tax%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Harris%20were%20to%20pursue%20legalization%2C%20there%20are%20two%20ways%20that%20she%20could%20do%20it%3A%20by%20signing%20federal%20legislation%20passed%20by%20Congress%2C%20or%20by%20moving%20to%20de-schedule%20the%20drug%20herself%2C%20though%20that%20process%20could%20also%20take%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20whether%20that%20would%20be%20a%20top%20priority%20issue%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20that%20we%20will%20see%20a%20potential%20Harris%20administration%20go%20much%20farther%20than%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%2C%26quot%3B%20Fox%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20to%20whether%20Harris%20should%20embrace%20the%20popularity%20of%20marijuana%20in%20her%20campaign%2C%20most%20lawmakers%20demurred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20never%20object%20to%20people%20who%20speak%20on%20my%20issues%2C%20but%20she's%20got%20a%20lot%20on%20her%20plate%2C%26quot%3B%20Blumenauer%20said.%20%26quot%3BShe's%20got%20lots%20of%20people%20to%20tell%20her%20what%20to%20do.%20I%20won't%20be%20one%20of%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkamala-harris-marijuana-legalization-stance-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727429402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f454240d59cc64f5b02ede%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkamala-harris-marijuana-legalization-stance-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Harris%20has%20long%20supported%20marijuana%20reforms%20and%20once%20backed%20legalization%2C%20but%20it%20remains%20unclear%20whether%20she%20would%20go%20further%20than%20Biden.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bmetzger%40insider.com%20(Bryan%20Metzger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkamala-harris-marijuana-legalization-stance-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kharge%20defends%20Karnataka%20govt's%20decision%20to%20withdraw%20consent%20given%20to%20CBI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727429395000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113735637%2Cimgsize-19402.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdelhi%2Fcongress-chief-mallikarjun-kharge-defends-karnataka-govts-decision-to-withdraw-general-consent-given-to-cbi%2Farticleshow%2F113735646.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Congress%20president%20M%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20defends%20Karnataka's%20withdrawal%20of%20general%20consent%20for%20CBI%20investigations%2C%20highlighting%20past%20misuse%20allegations.%20He%20asserts%20that%20this%20move%20is%20within%20the%20state's%20rights%20and%20recalls%20similar%20actions%20during%20former%20CM%20Devraj%20Urs'%20tenure.%20Kharge%20also%20mentioned%20previous%20high-profile%20cases%20where%20the%20CBI%20declined%20to%20in